quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  42,1,"Ḥā, Meem."
  42,2,"ʿAyn, Seen, Qāf.<sup foot_note=197293>1</sup>",footnotes:197293:1
  42,3,"Thus has He revealed to you, [O Muḥammad], and to those before you - Allāh, the Exalted in Might, the Wise."
  42,4,"To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, and He is the Most High, the Most Great.<sup foot_note=197294>1</sup>",footnotes:197294:1
  42,5,"The heavens almost break from above them,<sup foot_note=197295>1</sup> and the angels exalt [Allāh] with praise of their Lord and ask forgiveness for those on earth. Unquestionably, it is Allāh who is the Forgiving, the Merciful.",footnotes:197295:1
  42,6,"And those who take as allies other than Him - Allāh is [yet] Guardian over them; and you, [O Muḥammad], are not over them a manager."
  42,7,"And thus We have revealed to you an Arabic Qur’ān that you may warn the Mother of Cities [i.e., Makkah] and those around it<sup foot_note=197296>1</sup> and warn of the Day of Assembly, about which there is no doubt. A party will be in Paradise and a party in the Blaze.",footnotes:197296:1
  42,8,"And if Allāh willed, He could have made them [of] one religion, but He admits whom He wills<sup foot_note=197297>1</sup> into His mercy. And the wrongdoers have not any protector or helper.",footnotes:197297:1
  42,9,"Or have they taken protectors [or allies] besides Him? But Allāh - He is the Protector, and He gives life to the dead, and He is over all things competent."
  42,10,"And in anything over which you disagree - its ruling is [to be referred] to Allāh. [Say], "That is Allāh, my Lord; upon Him I have relied, and to Him I turn back."<sup foot_note=197298>1</sup>",footnotes:197298:1